-- China Picks 12 Cities for Trials of Merged Telecoms Networks, Sina Reports
-- Joshua Fellman
-- 2010-07-01T03:12:33Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-07-01/chinese-government-picks-12-cities-for-trials-of-merged-telecoms-networks.html

          
          
             China’s has picked 12 cities for 
trials of merged phone, Internet and television networks, the 
country’s central government said in statement dated yesterday 
and posted on its website today.
  The cities are Beijing, Shanghai, Harbin, Wuhan, Hangzhou, 
Nanjing, Shenzhen, Qingdao, Xiamen, Dalian, Mianyang and the 
Changsha-Xiangtan-Zhuzhou area of Hunan province, the statement
said.  
          
          


  


        